                    projectNumber="-"
                    uri="https://www.youtube.com/embed/hjqZW-tttfc?enablejsapi=1&amp;origin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abbvie.com&amp;widgetid=1&amp;forigin=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.abbvie.com%2Fwho-we-are%2Four-stories%2Fhow-medicinal-chemists-are-creating-new-weapons-against-autoimmune-diseases.html&amp;aoriginsup=1&amp;vf=1"
                    videoContentLayout="none"/>
                <block_5
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    analytics_id="-"
                    blockId="-"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="spacing-bottom,width-large"
                    filter="text-container"
                    language="none"
                    model="text-container"
                    modelFields="[classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Text Container">
                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Take rheumatoid arthritis (RA), for example, which is the most common form of autoimmune arthritis. RA is a chronic, systemic inflammatory disease that occurs when the body’s overactive immune cells mistakenly attack the joints, leading to painful and swollen joints, stiffness, fatigue, fever and loss of appetite.1 Yet, despite multiple treatment options that work in multiple different ways, most people living with RA have not achieved either low disease activity or clinical remission. Those are the primary goals of treatment, as defined by American College of Rheumatology guidelines.2,3&lt;/p>&lt;p>One reason that immune-mediated diseases like RA are tough to treat is that they involve complex signaling pathways. How does a medicinal chemist know where to focus their efforts for creating new a medicine?&lt;/p>&lt;p>“Believing in your science is key,” said Carolyn Cuff, Senior Director, Translational Immunology Department at the AbbVie Bioresearch Center. “Developing a specific strategy and hypothesis about why a new compound is different from other medicines in the class must be anchored in data, and then you have to trust that data to guide you forward.”&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_5>
                <block_6
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    attributionImage="https://delivery-p157365-e1665873.adobeaemcloud.com/adobe/assets/urn:aaid:aem:10664501-dab9-4695-b017-cb0c217c1348/as/carolyn-cuff-headshot.jpg"
                    attributionImageMimeType="image/unknown"
                    attributionName="Carolyn Cuff"
                    attributionRole="senior director, translational immunology, AbbVie Bioresearch Center"
                    backgroundImageAlt="\0"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_contentAlignment="quote-align-none"
                    classes_contentWidth="quote-content-col-none"
                    classes_theme="quote-none"
                    customClass="\0"
                    id="\0"
                    language="quote-standard,quote-h4"
                    model="quote"
                    modelFields="[quoteVariant,quotation,attributionName,attributionRole,attributionImage,attributionImageMimeType,quoteFragment,backgroundImage,backgroundImageAlt,backgroundImageMimeType,classes_customDynamicClass,blockId,classes_commonCustomClass,language,analytics_id]"
                    name="Quote"
                    quotation="&lt;p>Believing in your science is key.&lt;/p>"
                    quoteVariant="quote-standard"/>
                <block_7
                    jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                    sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block"
                    blockId="\0"
                    classes_customDynamicClass="h5-size,width-large"
